title: Grateful Dead Live at Irvine Meadows on 1984-04-07
lineage: CD -> Adobe Audition CC 2015 -> Samplitude Professional v11.2.1 -> FLAC
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, West L.A. Fadeaway, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Althea, CC Rider, Big Railroad Blues, My Brother Esau, Touch Of Gray

Set 2

Iko Iko, Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Drums-> Spanish Jam-> The Other One-> Throwing Stones-> Wharf Rat-> Not Fade Away, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text:
F'ing L.A. Round II with Pygmy & the Fellas of Madison,
Leaving Las Vegas was much like the Sheryl Crow song. 
Late night run in (what is packed now with smelly feet) Jack Straw, a 1981 4 door Chevrolet aka Animal House on Wheels......
Once inside I chose to Tape and the Sony ECM 50 stage right of the Soundboard on venue railing. Set-up is secure, solid, & quiet. 
D6 equally secure with moving gear & wires about. 
Band hit the Stage, I hit the pause button, and Feel like a Stranger begins to roll. At the same time I catch some LA bitch in my Gear Bag stealing Vegas Tapes. The whole episode is recorded and my last two words were "F'ing L.A."  Tape Masters went to Madison later that year during Cal Expo > Red Rocks adventure
